Based on the patient's profile, the top two choices of biological drugs would be Vedolizumab and Ustekinumab. 

Vedolizumab specifically targets the gut and has been shown to be effective in treating moderate to severe ulcerative colitis. It has a good safety profile and is less likely to cause systemic side effects. However, it may take longer to see the effects of the drug and it requires intravenous administration.

Ustekinumab is another option that could be considered. It is used in the treatment of multiple sclerosis as well as moderate to severe ulcerative colitis. It can be administered subcutaneously and may offer the convenience of home administration. However, it may have more systemic effects compared to Vedolizumab.

